1 Obtaining count data

1.1 Reading in data with tximeta

# define age groups
age_groups <- data.frame(Age = as.character(seq(1, 96, 1)), 
                         age_group = c(rep('1-15', 15), rep('16-26', 11), 
                                      rep('27-60', 34), rep('61-85', 25),
                                      rep('86-96', 11)), 
                         group1 = c(rep('Group1', 15), rep('rest', 81)),
                         group5 = c(rep('rest', 85), rep('Group5', 11)))
# get info about the runs
runs_info <- read.delim(paste0(dir, "Data/SraRunTable.txt"), sep = ",") %>%
  mutate(Age = gsub("y[rs]\\d+mos", "", Age)) %>%
  mutate(Age = gsub("yr", "", Age)) %>%
  left_join(age_groups) %>%
  mutate(age_group = factor(age_group, levels = unique(age_groups$age_group))) %>%
  filter(disease == "Normal") %>% 
  mutate(Age = as.numeric(Age))

2 Differential expression analysis with DESeq2

2.1 Group1-specific genes

dds <- DESeqDataSet(gse, design = ~ group1)
## using counts and average transcript lengths from tximeta
## Warning in DESeqDataSet(gse, design = ~group1): some variables in design formula
## are characters, converting to factors
# differential expression analysis
dds <- DESeq(dds)
## estimating size factors
## using 'avgTxLength' from assays(dds), correcting for library size
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
## -- replacing outliers and refitting for 448 genes
## -- DESeq argument 'minReplicatesForReplace' = 7 
## -- original counts are preserved in counts(dds)
## estimating dispersions
## fitting model and testing
# calculate log2 foldchange between age group 1 individuals and all others
DE1 <- results(dds, contrast=c("group1", "Group1", "rest"))
DE1$gene <- rowData(dds)$symbol
DE1 <- subset(DE1, select = c(gene, log2FoldChange, pvalue, padj)) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = "ensembl_id") %>%
  filter(gene != "") %>%
  drop_na(padj) %>%
  group_by(gene) %>% # mean over transcripts belonging to the same gene
  summarize(log2FoldChange = max(log2FoldChange), padj = min(padj)) %>%
  mutate(abs_log2_fc = abs(log2FoldChange)) %>%
  arrange(padj) %>%
  mutate(updown = ifelse(log2FoldChange > 0, 'up', 'down'))

DE1_200 <- slice_min(DE1, padj, n = 170)
write.csv(DE1_200, paste0(dir, "Data/DE_Group1.csv"), row.names = FALSE)
head(DE1_200)
## # A tibble: 6 × 5
##   gene    log2FoldChange     padj abs_log2_fc updown
##   <chr>            <dbl>    <dbl>       <dbl> <chr> 
## 1 MYO19            0.349 8.77e-22       0.349 up    
## 2 CCN5            -4.39  1.20e-19       4.39  down  
## 3 TRIM39           0.490 2.85e-18       0.490 up    
## 4 NDUFA6           0.262 3.06e-17       0.262 up    
## 5 PPP1R18          0.390 6.58e-17       0.390 up    
## 6 SELENOP         -4.05  1.02e-13       4.05  down
# Select top 200 up- and downregulated genes
DE1_down <- DE1 %>% filter(log2FoldChange < 0) %>% slice_min(padj, n = 170)
DE1_up <- DE1 %>% filter(log2FoldChange > 0) %>% slice_min(padj, n = 170)
write.csv(DE1_down, paste0(dir, "Data/DE_Group1_down.csv"), row.names = FALSE)
write.csv(DE1_up, paste0(dir, "Data/DE_Group1_up.csv"), row.names = FALSE)

2.2 Group5-specific genes

dds <- DESeqDataSet(gse, design = ~ group5)
## using counts and average transcript lengths from tximeta
## Warning in DESeqDataSet(gse, design = ~group5): some variables in design formula
## are characters, converting to factors
# differential expression analysis
dds <- DESeq(dds)
## estimating size factors
## using 'avgTxLength' from assays(dds), correcting for library size
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
## -- replacing outliers and refitting for 412 genes
## -- DESeq argument 'minReplicatesForReplace' = 7 
## -- original counts are preserved in counts(dds)
## estimating dispersions
## fitting model and testing
# calculate log2 foldchange between age group 1 individuals and all others
DE5 <- results(dds, contrast=c("group5", "Group5", "rest"))
DE5$gene <- rowData(dds)$symbol
DE5 <- subset(DE5, select = c(gene, log2FoldChange, pvalue, padj)) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = "ensembl_id") %>%
  filter(gene != "") %>%
  drop_na(padj) %>%
  group_by(gene) %>% # mean over transcripts belonging to the same gene
  summarize(log2FoldChange = max(log2FoldChange), padj = min(padj)) %>%
  mutate(abs_log2_fc = abs(log2FoldChange)) %>%
  arrange(desc(abs_log2_fc)) %>%
  mutate(updown = ifelse(log2FoldChange > 0, 'up', 'down'))

DE5_200 <- slice_min(DE5, padj, n = 170)
write.csv(DE5_200, paste0(dir, "Data/DE_Group5.csv"), row.names = FALSE)

2.3 Continuous age

dds <- DESeqDataSet(gse, design = ~ Age)
## using counts and average transcript lengths from tximeta
##   the design formula contains one or more numeric variables with integer values,
##   specifying a model with increasing fold change for higher values.
##   did you mean for this to be a factor? if so, first convert
##   this variable to a factor using the factor() function
##   the design formula contains one or more numeric variables that have mean or
##   standard deviation larger than 5 (an arbitrary threshold to trigger this message).
##   Including numeric variables with large mean can induce collinearity with the intercept.
##   Users should center and scale numeric variables in the design to improve GLM convergence.
# differential expression analysis
dds <- DESeq(dds)
## estimating size factors
## using 'avgTxLength' from assays(dds), correcting for library size
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
## -- replacing outliers and refitting for 219 genes
## -- DESeq argument 'minReplicatesForReplace' = 7 
## -- original counts are preserved in counts(dds)
## estimating dispersions
## fitting model and testing
# calculate log2 foldchange between age group 1 individuals and all others
DE <- results(dds)
DE$gene <- rowData(dds)$symbol
DE <- subset(DE, select = c(gene, log2FoldChange, pvalue, padj)) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = "ensembl_id") %>%
  filter(gene != "") %>%
  drop_na(padj) %>%
  filter(padj < 0.0000000001) %>%
  group_by(gene) %>% # mean over transcripts belonging to the same gene
  summarize(log2FoldChange = mean(log2FoldChange), padj = mean(padj)) %>%
  mutate(abs_log2_fc = abs(log2FoldChange)) %>%
  arrange(desc(abs_log2_fc)) %>%
  mutate(updown = ifelse(log2FoldChange > 0, 'up', 'down'))

write.csv(DE, paste0(dir, "Data/DE_cont.csv"), row.names = FALSE)
head(DE)

3 Intersection with DE genes of consecutive age groups

groups <- data.frame('transition'= c('fc_1-15_16-26', 'fc_16-26_27-60', 
                                     'fc_27-60_61-85', 'fc_61-85_86-96'),
                     'group' = c('Group 1 vs. Group 2', 'Group 2 vs. Group 3', 
                                 'Group 3 vs. Group 4', 'Group 4 vs. Group 5'))
all_groups <- c('Group 1 vs. Group 2', 'Group 2 vs. Group 3', 'Group 3 vs. Group 4', 
                'Group 4 vs. Group 5', 'Group 1 vs. all others', 'Group 5 vs. all others')
all_DE <- read.delim(paste0(dir, "Data/DE_var_p_n_200.csv"), sep = ",") %>%
  left_join(groups) %>%
  subset(select = c(gene, group)) %>%
  bind_rows(data.frame('gene' = DE1_200$gene, 'group' = 'Group 1 vs. all others'))  %>%
  bind_rows(data.frame('gene' = DE5_200$gene, 'group' = 'Group 5 vs. all others')) %>%
  mutate(group = factor(group, levels = all_groups)) %>%
  group_by(group) %>% 
  group_split()
## Joining, by = "transition"
names(all_DE) <- all_groups
all_DE <- lapply(all_DE, function(list) list$gene)

upset(fromList(all_DE), order.by = "freq", 
       mainbar.y.label = "Intersections", sets.x.label = "DE Genes",
       text.scale = c(3.5, 3.5, 3, 3, 3.5, 3.5), nintersects = 20,
       keep.order= TRUE, sets = c("Group 5 vs. all others", "Group 4 vs. Group 5", "Group 3 vs. Group 4", 
                                  "Group 2 vs. Group 3", "Group 1 vs. Group 2", "Group 1 vs. all others"))

all_groups <- c('Group 4&5 vs. all others', 'Group 5 vs. all others')
all_DE <- read.delim(paste0(dir, "Data/DE_Group45_down.csv"), sep = ",") %>%
  mutate(group = 'Group 4&5 vs. all others') %>%
  subset(select = c(gene, group)) %>%
  bind_rows(data.frame('gene' = DE5_down$gene, 'group' = 'Group 5 vs. all others'))  %>%
  mutate(group = factor(group, levels = all_groups)) %>%
  group_by(group) %>% 
  group_split()
names(all_DE) <- all_groups
all_DE <- lapply(all_DE, function(list) list$gene)

upset(fromList(all_DE), order.by = "freq", 
       mainbar.y.label = "Intersections", sets.x.label = "DE Genes",
       text.scale = c(3.5, 3.5, 3, 3, 3.5, 3.5), nintersects = 20,
       keep.order= TRUE, sets = c("Group 5 vs. all others", "Group 4&5 vs. all others"))

all_groups <- c('Group 4&5 vs. all others', 'Group 5 vs. all others')
all_DE <- read.delim(paste0(dir, "Data/DE_Group45_up.csv"), sep = ",") %>%
  mutate(group = 'Group 4&5 vs. all others') %>%
  subset(select = c(gene, group)) %>%
  bind_rows(data.frame('gene' = DE5_up$gene, 'group' = 'Group 5 vs. all others'))  %>%
  mutate(group = factor(group, levels = all_groups)) %>%
  group_by(group) %>% 
  group_split()
names(all_DE) <- all_groups
all_DE <- lapply(all_DE, function(list) list$gene)

upset(fromList(all_DE), order.by = "freq", 
       mainbar.y.label = "Intersections", sets.x.label = "DE Genes",
       text.scale = c(3.5, 3.5, 3, 3, 3.5, 3.5), nintersects = 20,
       keep.order= TRUE, sets = c("Group 5 vs. all others", "Group 4&5 vs. all others"))
